Take care of yourself and your loved ones, thats the most important thing right now. Stay safe, stay at home and follow the rules experts are giving to us so we will improve this situation with time, for ourselves and others. Thanks for the cheers, support, its always welcome!! Love you guys, I wish the best for you too!! 
Also a lot of love to my Italian friends, stay strong, we will try our best too in Spain.

Para todos los españoles, espero también que la situación vaya mejorando, debemos dar lo mejor de nosotros, permanecer en casa y seguir las recomendaciones de los expertos. No sé si las cosas se endurecerán con los días pero esperemos que si es así esto haga mejorar las cosas. Ánimos!!

snippet.textDisplay:
I don't know if you saw this comment. For 7 years ARMY. So since the day you debuted. write this text from the translation. I would be glad if you are not concerned with the typo. But I love South Korea very much. Even when the coronavirus began to spread, it was you and the citizens of South Korea that came to my mind first. When I wrote this comment, a news came. The coronavirus test of our lower neighbor was positive. And he was urgently moved to quarantine by ambulance. I hope the apartment I live in is not quarantined. It will be disinfected in a few hours. Let me continue where I left off. I can imagine how boring it is to receive such messages from the Turks all the time. I will not call you to Turkey. The fact that others insist on this makes me angry. Because in this case you cannot do anything. I've been trying to earn a high school in Seoul for the last 2 years. I started working as soon as primary school was finished in order to win the high school I wanted. I've been dealing with South Korea since I was born. Because one of our family friends became veterans in the Korean War. He always told me about the Korean War and the hospitable citizens of South Korea. That's how I got to know you. The world knows South Korea thanks to BTS. I have always looked at you from different angles. For example; I became ARMY not because you are so handsome, but because you are valuable and kind people. My favorite member among you is PARK JİMİN. And that's why the girls I met at school constantly quarrel with me and exclude me. Because they Jimin love much. It's ridiculous for them to act like this because they love Jimin. I was 6 when I first saw you. And for 7 years I said to you my brother. I have previously filed a complaint with the Ministry of Family and Social Policies. There was domestic violence. When I was 12 years old, I had a psychologist. And we got over this problem. They don't interfere with my love for South Korea. But they will never let me realize my dreams there. I don't know why I wrote this text. Because I have reached all your albums for 7 years. But I can't reach you. For example, it is a dream for me to attend your fan meetings or concerts. I am so bored to see you on posters and computer screens.
All I want is you to believe me. Because nobody believes me about this.
I LOVE YOU… YOU WILL ALWAYS BE VALUABLE FOR ME…

We are all so lucky to have BTS, this caring, kind group of people who want us to be safe and happy. For all you new ARMYs out there, you may not know all their names, but just know you've picked an awesome fandom. Be safe, BTS, and everyone watching this and reading my comment. We may live in different countries or states and speak different mother tongues, but we all need to stay safe during this time. Wash your hands often, try to stay away from sick-looking people, and protect your loved ones. With the help of important breakthroughs in medicine and tirelessly working scientists, we will survive this pandemic together. Stay strong, love BTS, and stay safe.

Tradução PT/BR:
RM: Para os Armys em todo o mundo e para todos que assistem isso, digamos olá.
BTS: 1, 2, 3, Olá, somos bts.
RM: Estamos aqui porque os cadetes da academia de enfermagem das forças armadas da Coréia, nos escolheu para fazer o próximo vídeo para apoiar a luta contra o covid-19.
JH: Queremos agradecer aos oficiais de enfermagem, equipe médica e todos que lutam contra esse vírus para proteger a vida e a vida das pessoas.
JN: Percebemos mais do que nunca como nossa vida cotidiana era significativa, de pé no palco diante de assentos vazios, percebemos o quão precioso era cada momento com você.
SG: covid-19 interrompeu as viagens e as pessoas mantêm distância entre si, eu acho que a coisa mais difícil pode ser isso, estamos nos sentindo cada vez mais isolados.
JM: Mas gente, somos enganados de perto e sentimos dor e alegria, se tivermos coragem e superarmos qualquer coisa, tenho certeza de que teremos sucesso com o poder de nossa conexão.
JK: Atualmente precisamos confiar mais que duvidar, cuidar mais do outro, como cidadãos da Coréia e do mundo, o BTS enfrentará esse desafio junto com todos vocês.
V: Espero que em breve possamos ver novamente aqueles que amamos, compartilhar uma refeição e conversar juntos, espero que em breve possamos cantar e ser felizes juntos com vocês.
RM: Pessoal, vamos esperar que as coisas voltem ao normal e fazer o nosso melhor onde estamos, então, que tal fazer nossa alegria? Vamos juntar as mãos.
BTS : BANGTAN! VAMOS COREIA! FIQUE FORTE COREIA! ARMYS FIQUEM FORTES!
RM: Fiquem todos fortes e seguros! I Peuple U
